    "markdown": "---\ntitle: \"003 — OEM–state network evolution\"\ndate: 2026-06-11\n---\n\n## Question\n\nTreating the market as a bipartite OEM–state network (edge = OEM holds ≥0.5%\nshare in a state), how did topology — density, modularity, communities —\nshift across the BS6 transition (2020), COVID, and the EV era?\n\n## Setup\n\n::: {#a13635fd .cell execution_count=1}\n``` {.python .cell-code}\nimport duckdb\nimport pandas as pd\nimport plotly.express as px\nfrom complexity_lab.config import settings\nfrom complexity_lab.networks import build as nb, metrics as nm\n\ncon = duckdb.connect(str(settings.db_path), read_only=True)\nedges = con.execute(\"SELECT * FROM oem_state_edges\").df()\nLATEST_FULL = int(edges.year.max()) - 1\n```\n:::\n\n\n## Topology over time\n\n::: {#131bad3f .cell execution_count=2}\n``` {.python .cell-code}\ngraphs = {y: nb.share_weighted_graph(e) for y, e in edges.groupby(\"year\") if y <= LATEST_FULL}\nevo = nm.temporal_metric_series(graphs).reset_index()\npx.line(evo, x=\"period\", y=[\"density\", \"modularity\"], markers=True,\n        title=\"Bipartite network density & modularity by year\")\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div style=\"height:525px; width:100%;\">            <script src=\"https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/mathjax/2.7.5/MathJax.js?config=TeX-AMS-MML_SVG\"></script><script>if (window.MathJax && window.MathJax.Hub && window.MathJax.Hub.Config) {window.MathJax.Hub.Config({SVG: {font: \"STIX-Web\"}});}</script>                <script>window.PlotlyConfig = {MathJaxConfig: 'local'};</script>\n        <script charset=\"utf-8\" src=\"https://cdn.plot.ly/plotly-3.6.0.min.js\" integrity=\"sha256-QaOVwtVY0T02VaHrr6pnoHLCwayMJp4O5n4YyaE3rJk=\" crossorigin=\"anonymous\"></script>                <div id=\"ec586424-f6e4-4aab-b5e7-fafc52d05c7c\" class=\"plotly-graph-div\" style=\"height:100%; width:100%;\"></div>            <script>                window.PLOTLYENV=window.PLOTLYENV || {};            